items.name: Deep-Learning-and-Machine-Learning-Based-Early-Diagnosis-of-Alzheimers-from-MRI---Clinical-Data
items.description: An advanced machine learning framework for early Alzheimer's diagnosis, integrating MRI imaging with clinical data. Using a fine-tuned VGG16 CNN for brain scans and an SVM model for clinical indicators, NeuroDetect ensures precise classification, aiding researchers, neurologists, and healthcare applications in neurodegenerative disease detection.

items.name: pfund
items.description: An All-in-One Algo-Trading Framework: Backtest -> Train -> Trade -> Monitor. Machine / Deep Learning Ready. Supports All Trading: TradFi+CeFi+DeFi. Code Once, Trade Anywhere.

items.description: An open-source machine learning framework for global analyses of parton distributions.

items.name: LightGBM
items.description: A fast, distributed, high performance gradient boosting (GBT, GBDT, GBRT, GBM or MART) framework based on decision tree algorithms, used for ranking, classification and many other machine learning tasks.

items.name: symphonyGPT
items.description: A platform developed from an open framework to help AI researchers and developers to rapidly prototype, test and deploy workflows that include machine learning models as worker components. The workflow can be invoked on command line or web service, as well as integrated into UX/UI as part of a larger intelligent solution.

items.name: ryzen-ai-documentation
items.description: Onboarding documentation source for the AMD Ryzen AI Software Platform.   The AMD Ryzen AI Software Platform enables developers to take pretrained machine learning models in popular frameworks and run them on laptops powered by AMD Ryzen AI technology.

items.name: tensorflow-federated
items.description: An open-source framework for machine learning and other computations on decentralized data.

items.name: ICU-Risk-Predictor
items.description: A machine learning framework for ICU patient risk assessment and mortality prediction using physiological time-series data.

items.name: Self-Driving-Car-JS
items.description: This project demonstrates a complete self-driving car simulation built entirely with vanilla JavaScript, without using any external libraries or machine learning frameworks.

items.name: ScaleExplorer
items.description: ScaleExplorer is a simulation framework that enables agile exploration over the large machine learning model design and optimization space. This new capability will unlock efficiency and sustainability optimization opportunities to flexibly adapt to the constantly-changing training environment.

items.name: AutoMol-v2
items.description: The AutoMol Framework is a multi-phase computational pipeline designed for the automated generation, analysis, and testing of novel molecular structures. This system integrates machine learning techniques, molecular dynamics simulations, and bioinformatics tools to create and optimize molecules tailored to specific biological functions.

items.name: equitrain
items.description: Equitrain: A Unified Framework for Training and Fine-tuning Machine Learning Interatomic Potentials

items.name: GelGenie
items.description: Open-Source package for segmentation and analysis of gel electrophoresis images using machine learning.  Both a python framework for training/running models and a QuPath GUI extension are available.

items.name: npmod
items.description: Building a simple deep learning framework and some machine learning/deep learning models from scratch (pure Numpy and Pytorch)

items.name: oikan
items.description: OIKAN is a neuro-symbolic machine learning framework inspired by Kolmogorov-Arnold representation theorem. It combines the power of modern neural networks with techniques for extracting clear, interpretable symbolic formulas from data. OIKAN is designed to make machine learning models both accurate and Interpretable.

items.name: heat-vulnerability-research
items.description: A machine learning-based geospatial framework for urban heat vulnerability mapping in India using high-resolution spatial, climate, and socio-economic data.

items.name: TORCS-Self-Driving-Car-AI
items.description: A Python-based framework for TORCS that enables data collection from manual driving sessions and trains AI drivers using machine learning models such as Decision Trees, Random Forests, and MLP Regressors.

items.name: Space-Radiation-Tolerant
items.description: Space Labs AI presents: A radiation-tolerant machine learning framework enabling neural networks to operate reliably in space environments. Features adaptive protection, Reed-Solomon error correction, and breakthrough architecture optimizations that improve performance under radiation.

items.name: AsTRiQue
items.description: ASk The RIght QUEstions: An active machine learning framework for perception experiments

items.name: graphstorm
items.description: Enterprise graph machine learning framework for billion-scale graphs for ML scientists and data scientists.

items.description: The main reposititory that holds the submodules for the analysis on the impact of different intermediate language representations of the Dragon Type Identification Machine Learning Framework

items.name: sagemaker-distribution
items.description: A set of Docker images that include popular frameworks for machine learning, data science and visualization.

items.name: ModelingToolkit.jl
items.description: An acausal modeling framework for automatically parallelized scientific machine learning (SciML) in Julia. A computer algebra system for integrated symbolics for physics-informed machine learning and automated transformations of differential equations

items.name: Cross_Domain_Predictive_Analytics_Dashboard
items.description: An advanced web-based data platform using Python frameworks that integrates multiple data sources and applies machine learning for predictive analytics.

items.name: An-Efficient-Distributed-Machine-Learning-Inference-Framework-with-Byzantine-Fault-Detection
items.description: An Efficient Distributed Machine Learning Inference Framework with Byzantine Fault Detection

items.name: UTScan
items.description: UTScan is a hybrid machine learning framework that quantifies daily urban travel intensity using continuous seismic noise recordings. Leveraging CatBoost and LSTM, UTScan extracts features from the 220Hz seismic power spectrum to deliver accurate, generalizable travel predictions across regions and time periods.

items.name: DMAIC-Food-Delivery-Project
items.description: Analyze food delivery performance using the Lean Six Sigma DMAIC framework. Includes visual insights, control charts, and a machine learning model to predict late orders.

items.name: Infosys-Model-Inference-Library
items.description: IMIL is a versatile and powerful tool designed to simplify the deployment and utilization of machine learning models, regardless of the framework or model type.

items.name: adas
items.description: ADAS (Advanced Driving Autonomous System) is a modular, full-stack framework for building and deploying self-driving car technologies. It includes machine learning workflows, backend services, a GraphQL API, and a user-friendly frontendorganized into clean, decoupled modules for flexibility and scalability.

items.name: Deef_Fake-Detection
items.description: Deepfake Detection is a machine learning project that identifies whether a video is real or fake. The model is trained on real video data to learn natural facial patterns and detects deepfakes by spotting inconsistencies in facial features or movements. Built using Python and deep learning frameworks.

items.name: heat
items.description: Distributed tensors and Machine Learning framework with GPU and MPI acceleration in Python

items.name: pennylane-qrack
items.description: The PennyLane-Qrack plugin integrates the Qrack quantum computing framework with PennyLane's quantum machine learning capabilities.

items.description: A flexible and performant framework for training machine learning potentials.

items.name: ml-framework-kagglemonthly
items.description: A machine learning framework designed for Kaggle competitions with a focus on tabular data processing

items.name: MLContainerLab
items.description: A collection of curated machine learning frameworks dockerized for local experimentation and seamless scaling to cloud compute platforms. MLContainerLab provides modular, reproducible, and optimized environments to streamline ML workflows from research to deployment.

items.name: FedEasy
items.description: FedEasy is an intuitive powerful yet simple to use Federated Learning framework. Our goal is to streamline the process of setting up and running federated learning experiments with ease, making advanced machine learning techniques accessible to researchers and developers alike.

items.name: GreatLakes-TempSensors
items.description: Collaborative repository for optimizing the placement of temperature sensors in the Great Lakes using the DeepSensor machine learning framework. Aiming to enhance the quantitative understanding of surface temperature variability for better environmental monitoring and decision-making.

items.name: Reinforce4J
items.description: Reinforce4j is a Java library designed for implementing reinforcement learning algorithms, with a primary focus on Monte Carlo Tree Search (MCTS). It provides tools and frameworks for building agents that can learn to play games, demonstrated with examples like Tic-Tac-Toe and Connect 4. The library supports integration with machine learning models

Built in Python with Flask frontend, powered by UCI CKD dataset. Achieves 100% accuracy through feature  ensemble modeling.

items.name: sentinelcam
items.description: A computer vision and machine learning pipeline on a distributed framework. Designed for an embedded network on low voltage IoT hardware.
